description:
Hello all!
The "Brocante Les puces Nautiques" will be soon.
This is a "brocante" specially for underwater lovers like us, where you can find diving equipment (new and used), information, food and drinks and there is usually a nice atmosphere.
Maybe a nice place to meet before our first "official meeting" on June 5th?

I will be passing by around 15h.
If anyone will like to join, get on the list and we will define later the exact meeting place :-)
name: Brocante les Puces Nautiques

description:
Lets met up for a drink and a dive (optional) in the deepest diving pool in the world. 


If you will like to join us for the dive, remember to bring your certification card.

See you soon!

venue.name: Nemo33
venue.address_1: Rue de Stalle 333 (Rond-point des Menhirs), 1180 Uccle (Brussels)

how_to_find_us: we will be at the entrance of the building
name: Let's meet up for a dive and a drink !

description:
Hello scuba diving lovers!!

It is GREAT to see that we are already 26 divers in this group!  

I was a bit away since last event, but now that I am back from Sardegna I am hoping that we can meet soon!  

Should we plan a dive and a dinner/drink in the terrace of Nemo33?

(Last time we were a few, but it was cool to do a relaxing dive and to have a drink together :-)

How many of you will be available on Sunday 10th august? 

What I propose is that we reserve the "package Dive + Dinner" of 23 euro (MINIMUM 10 DIVERS).

The price of a dive is around 20 euro.... so worth it to take the package ;-)

Vamos! Lets meet underwater and enjoy a nice dinner together in the beautiful terrace of Nemo33!

Hasta pronto bajo el agua!

Paula

venue.name: Nemo33
venue.address_1: Rue de Stalle 333 (Rond-point des Menhirs), 1180 Uccle (Brussels)

how_to_find_us: :-) The divers, we will meet at 18h15 for registration (don't forget certification cards). The non-divers that want to join for the drink, see you at 20h15 at the terrace (table reserved for Paula).  See you on sunday!
name: A dive and a terrace?

description:
Hello all!
Why not exploring this time the "Barrage de l'eau d'heure"?
Yes, ok, it might not be the Caribbean ... but its a new adventure not far from Brussels!!!  After the dive: hot chocolate apero  ;-)

To have in mind:
There is a filling station over there (in the case you have your own tank).
If you do not have a tank, or you need to rent some gear, No worries! We can suggest you a couple of places in Brussels were you can rent it!


More info to come for those interested!

iii Who is in for this new adventure?

LETS DO IT!!!!
name: Barrage de l'eau d'heure... and chocolat chaud!
